Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/astronomy-and-space-science-programs-in-turkey.webp","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/astronomy-and-space-science-programs-in-turkey.webp","width":"1168","height":"880","inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/astronomy-and-space-science-programs-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/astronomy-and-space-science-programs-in-turkey/","name":"Astronomy and Space Science Programs in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-02-20T09:26:20+03:00","dateModified":"2026-02-20T09:26:20+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"primaryImageOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/astronomy-and-space-science-programs-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Astronomy and Space Science Programs in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-02-20T09:26:20+03:00","dateModified":"2026-02-20T09:26:20+03:00","articleSection":"University and Programs","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Astronomy and Space Science may sound romantic, but it involves a lot of math, physics and observation. Turkey is a country full of surprises for","name":"Astronomy and Space Science Programs in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/astronomy-and-space-science-programs-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/astronomy-and-space-science-programs-in-turkey/#webpage"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/astronomy-and-space-science-programs-in-turkey.webp"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/astronomy-and-space-science-programs-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Astronomy and Space Science may sound romantic, but it involves a lot of math, physics and observation. Turkey is a country full of surprises for international students who want to study this field. It draws attention with both high quality academic staff and active observatories.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">With its geographical location, Turkey is really advantageous for <strong>observing the sky</strong>. Especially in the summer months, the number of cloudless nights is quite high. In addition, research centers used worldwide such as <strong><a href="https://tug.tubitak.gov.tr/" data-type="link" data-id="https://tug.tubitak.gov.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><mark style="color:#164292" class="has-inline-color">TÜBİTAK National Observatory</mark></a></strong> are also located here. This enables students to gain not only theoretical but also practical observation skills.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The medium of instruction is English at many universities and the departments are open to international students. <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-visa-application-process/" data-type="link" data-id="https://roadtostudy.com/en/student-visa-application-process/"><strong>The university application process in Turkey</strong></a> is not as complicated as you might think. You can apply to these departments through exams such as YÖS.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">As of 2025, the field of space and astronomy is gaining momentum in Turkey. Thanks to the work of the Space Agency, increased investments and international cooperation, job opportunities for graduates are also expanding.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="bogazici-university-both-scientific-and-scenic">Boğaziçi University: Both Scientific and Scenic</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">How does studying astrophysics overlooking the sea in Istanbul sound? <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/bogazici-universitesi/" data-type="link" data-id="https://roadtostudy.com/bogazici-universitesi/">Boğaziçi University,</a> one of Turkey&#8217;s most prestigious schools in this field. Astronomy courses under the physics department develop both theoretical knowledge and analytical thinking.</p>


<blockquote class="wp-block-quote">


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">One of the biggest advantages of Bosphorus is that it is offered entirely in English as the medium of instruction. This is a great advantage for international students. It also has an active student life in observational activities thanks to its proximity to <strong><a href="https://bogazici.edu.tr/tr/campuses/kandilli-kampusu/7" data-type="link" data-id="https://bogazici.edu.tr/tr_TR/Content/Kampus_Yasami/Kampusler/Kandilli_Kampusu" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Kandilli Observatory</a></strong>.</p>


</blockquote>


<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The academic staff is actively involved in international publications. Among the graduates, there are both those who pursue academic careers and those who work in space agencies.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="istanbul-university-turkeys-astronomy-fortress">Istanbul University: Turkey&#8217;s Astronomy Fortress</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">One of the first schools that comes to mind when it comes to Astronomy and Space Sciences in Turkey is definitely <strong><a href="https://astronomi-fen.istanbul.edu.tr/tr/_" data-type="link" data-id="https://astronomi-fen.istanbul.edu.tr/tr/_" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Istanbul University.</a></strong> This department is perfect for students who want to specialize directly in this field. Because you do not have a separate faculty, you have a direct Department of Astronomy and Space Sciences.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The university&#8217;s Observatory Application and Research Center provides observational training to students. In addition, master&#8217;s and doctoral programs are also actively carried out. The curriculum ranges from astrophysics to spectroscopy. If you want to understand the sky, not just watch it, this place is for you.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The department contributes a lot to local and foreign academic publications. Since Istanbul University also teaches in Turkish, the language barrier can be a problem, but it is also an opportunity for international students who want to learn Turkish.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="ege-university-a-giant-known-for-his-observatories">Ege University: A Giant Known for His Observatories</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">What would it be like to study astronomy in the sun-drenched city of Izmir? Ege University is one of the universities with the longest history in this field in Turkey. The Astronomy and Space Sciences department has been active since the 1960s and having its own observatory is a big plus.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><strong><a href="https://gozlemevi.ege.edu.tr/" data-type="link" data-id="https://gozlemevi.ege.edu.tr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Ege University Observatory (EÜG)</a>,</strong> is one of the places where students gain experience not only through lectures but also through real observation projects. Moreover, the department offers both undergraduate and graduate programs. The research network is particularly focused on variable stars and galaxies.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Living conditions in Izmir are also very comfortable for international students. With its warm climate, easy-to-reach campus and student-friendly environment, life outside of education is also enjoyable. You also have the chance to directly apply practical knowledge through activities such as the Observatory summer camp.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="odtu-the-summit-of-theoretical-knowledge">ODTÜ: The Summit of Theoretical Knowledge</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><a href="https://roadtostudy.com/orta-dogu-teknik-universitesi-tanitim-rehberi/" data-type="link" data-id="https://roadtostudy.com/orta-dogu-teknik-universitesi-tanitim-rehberi/"><strong>Middle East Technical University (METU)</strong></a> is one of the most prestigious technical universities in Turkey. The astronomy courses offered under the Department of Physics significantly improve both your theoretical and analytical thinking skills. Since the medium of instruction is English, it is a popular choice especially for international students.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">ODTÜ&#8217;s strong academic infrastructure makes it competitive not only in Turkey but also internationally. Astronomy is not offered directly as an undergraduate major, but it is possible to focus on this field with special elective courses in the physics undergraduate program. At the master&#8217;s and doctoral level, there are more areas of specialization.</p>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Campus life is very lively and the astronomy club is active among the students. Through activities such as telescope observations, seminars and national science festivals, interaction with students outside the department is also ensured.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="what-astronomy-and-space-science-courses-offer">What Astronomy and Space Science Courses Offer</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you&#8217;re studying Astronomy and Space Sciences, you have to accept up front that it&#8217;s not just about stargazing. The curriculum is intense and varied. Here&#8217;s what to expect:</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="basic-courses-you-will-take-in-the-first-two-years">Basic Courses You Will Take in the First Two Years:</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Mathematics</strong>: Analysis, differential equations, linear algebra</li>



<li><strong>Physics</strong>: Classical mechanics, electromagnetism, thermodynamics</li>



<li><strong>Computer</strong>: Introduction to programming (Python in some universities)</li>



<li><strong>General Astronomy</strong>: Celestial bodies and basic observation knowledge</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="specialty-courses-in-the-third-and-fourth-year">Specialty Courses in the Third and Fourth Year:</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Astrophysics</strong></li>



<li><strong>Spectroscopy</strong></li>



<li><strong>Sky Mechanics</strong></li>



<li><strong>Galaxy Structure and Evolution</strong></li>



<li><strong>Cosmology and Big Bang Theories</strong></li>



<li><strong>The Formation and Evolution of Stars</strong></li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="applied-and-supportive-lessons">Applied and Supportive Lessons:</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Laboratory Applications</strong>: Optical experiments, data analysis</li>



<li><strong>Telescope Training</strong>: Observation techniques, night observations</li>



<li><strong>Software and Data Analysis</strong>: Python, MATLAB, data processing for astronomy</li>
</ul>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Since modern astronomy is now completely intertwined with digital data, software knowledge and data literacy have become an integral part of these programs.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="base-points-for-the-department-of-astrophysics-2025-where-do-you-stand">Base Points for the Department of Astrophysics 2025: Where Do You Stand?</h2>



<p class="wp-block-paragraph">If you want to study Astronomy and Space Sciences or Astrophysics in Turkey, you can apply with exams like YÖS or SAT. But of course, scores are also important. The admission criteria of each university is different and changes slightly every year. Official data for 2025 has not yet been published, but the general picture according to 2024 scores is as follows:</p>


<figure class="wp-block-table">
<table class="has-fixed-layout">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>University</th>
<th>Department</th>
<th>Type of Exam</th>
<th>2024 Base Score (Estimated)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Istanbul University</td>
<td>Astronomy and Space Sciences</td>
<td>YÖS</td>
<td>75</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Ege University</td>
<td>Astronomy and Space Sciences</td>
<td>YÖS</td>
<td>72</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Boğaziçi University</td>
<td>Physics (including Astronomy)</td>
<td>SAT / Diploma</td>
<td>SAT Math: 700+</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>ODTÜ</td>
<td>Physics (including theoretical astrophysics)</td>
<td>SAT / Diploma</td>
<td>SAT Math: 730+</td>
</tr>
